7:
Come out already. I know you're
there.
11:
Quade Arsalett...
This is where you meet your end!
13:
Damn. You went and found out my
last name. You really hunkered
down and did your research, huh?
15:
And here I was, thinking you were
completely incompetent. 
Maybe I misjudged you?
19:
Eh, or maybe I didn't. You never
learn. I won't be beaten, not this way.
23:
Flashy as always. 
Not sure why I dragged 
myself out here. 
You seem fine on your own.
26:
These guys from our favorite
organization? Or are they from the
Farlands?
33:
*sigh* That's the one answer I didn't
want to hear, Quade.
37:
If you keep this up, you'll get yourself
killed, you know.
41:
I know. That would really ruin my
day.
45:
At least pretend to be concerned
when you say that.
47:
Well, in that case... Allow this old
man to introduce you to a certain
somebody.
51:
You mean... Alk and the others?! Yes!
To think that I can finally meet
them...
54:
You really do know too much for
your own good, kid.
58:
Anyway, I'd appreciate it if you could
welcome him already.
67:
H-hold on a minute, Stella! He hasn't
even said a single WORD yet!
70:
I think we're going to need a bit
more of an explanation than that...
75:
He knows too much. He flies off the
rails sometimes. I need you to look
after him. The end.
79:
Well that was.... concise, I guess?
Doesn't exactly put my mind at
ease... Smells like trouble, really.
82:
It was a short explanation, but it
basically hit all the correct points.
84:
The name is Quade Arsalett.
Pleasure to make your
acquaintance.
91:
Oh? You sure it's okay to give away
your family name just like that?
95:
I already know so much about
them—I figured it was only fair to
even the playing field.
98:
You are the decorated heroes who
helped defend Palpebra from the
dragon attack AND defeated the
flying golems, are you not?
102:
I'm somewhat of a spy, you see. 
I specialize in intelligence—and I've
had my eye on your group for quite
a while now!
106:
He's a big help to Kugala. We've had
him look into that one organization
we've been after as well.
110:
But I'm afraid I may have gone and
made myself—and my
origins—known to all the wrong
people.
114:
You mentioned something about a
family name earlier... What was that
about?
117:
Have you ever heard of a city called
Tiatha, by any chance?
122:
Yes. Tiatha is a port city situated to
the southeast of Palpebra. It was
once a prosperous place with a long
history.
124:
However, Palpebra's rapid
development has reversed the
power balance. Tiatha has been
practically absorbed into Palpebra,
and the two have a joint partnership.
126:
The merchant family that rules
Tiatha are known as the Arsaletts.
130:
How wonderfully knowledgeable you
are! Indeed, I am the second son of
the Arsalett family—disinherited
though I may be.
135:
You're a spy here, but you're also
from the ruling family of Palpebra's
biggest rival? How does that work?
139:
Your suspicion of me is written all
over your face.
142:
Both Tiatha and the Arsalett family
failed to keep up with the times and
have declined—that much is evident.
144:
As their disinherited son, all I want is
to be at the forefront of major
events—to ensure that I do not
repeat the same mistake again.
147:
That's why you became a spy? But...
wouldn't that mean trouble for the
Guild?
151:
If people found out his true identity,
sure. You'd want to keep him from
the front lines.
153:
Though interestingly enough, Kugala
didn't seem to share that opinion.
158:
All that being said, now that our
enemy has sniffed out my identity, 
I have no choice but to go into hiding.
161:
That's why I was hoping you'd let me
in!
169:
Listen here, Alk. You've got a bit of a
debt to me, don't you?
171:
Would you be a dear and welcome
the poor kid?
188:
Incredible! Every single one of those
is a different world?!
191:
To tell you the truth, the whole bit
about "going into hiding" was...
somewhat exaggerated.
194:
The biggest reason I did this was to
meet you guys—it's all about who
you know, after all.
196:
And now YOU know a spy. I'm sure I'll
be able to sniff out some valuable
information to help you in your
journey.
199:
Doing away with old, useless
traditions and forging new paths
ahead... Now THIS is the type of work
I can get behind!
203:
Right, right. Just remembered I had
one more thing to tell you, Alk.
206:
He's a liar. So, uh, be careful.
You need to learn to deal with
people like that, so just think of it as...
practice.
214:
*sigh* Now I have even more on my
plate to worry about...
